#Text=The Utah Jazz ( 24 - 35 ) defeated the Memphis Grizzlies ( 42 - 17 ) 93 - 82 on Tuesday at Fed Ex Forum Arena in Memphis .
#Text=In a surprise performance , the Jazz were able to take down one of the best teams in their conference , while notching their third straight victory as well .
#Text=They were the superior shooters in this one , going 45 percent from the field , while the Grizzlies finished at 40 percent .

#Text=The Jazz also secured a hefty advantage on the boards , as they out - rebounded the Grizzlies 55 - 37 , which may have made the biggest difference in their 11 - point win on the road in Memphis .
#Text=As they 've done all season long , Gordon Hayward and Derrick Favors did the bulk of the work offensively .
#Text=Hayward went 9 - for - 19 from the field , but missed all six of his three - point attempts , to finish with 21 points , while adding eight rebounds and six assists as well .

#Text=He 's been absolutely awful from deep over his last five games , going a combined 2 - for - 20 from the three - point line during that stretch , but he was able to overcome the poor shooting and still finish above his season scoring average of 20 points per game .
#Text=Favors , on the other hand , posted 21 points ( 8 - 14 FG , 5 - 6 FT ) of his own , to go along with six rebounds , two steals and three blocked shots .
#Text=He 's stepped it up offensively of late , averaging 19 points and 9 rebounds over his last four games .
#Text=He 's also posted three blocks in each of his last three games .
#Text=Notching one of his more impressive lines of his season , Rudy Gobert recorded 15 points ( 6 - 10 FG , 3 - 4 FT ) and 24 reobunds in 36 minutes .
#Text=He looks to be getting more and more comfortable as a member of the starting lineup , posting a double - double in three of his last four games .
#Text=The rebounds were a season - high .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Rodney Hood added 13 points ( 3 - 5 FG , 2 - 4 3Pt , 5 - 5 FT ) in 14 minutes .
#Text=Courtney Lee had the strongest performance of all the Grizzlies ' starters .
#Text=He went 7 - for - 13 from the field and 2 - for - 7 from the three - point line to finish with 18 points , while adding five rebounds as well .
#Text=One of the more inconsistent players on this team , it was one of his better nights , as he averages just 11 points per game on the season .
#Text=Marc Gasol also did everything he could to keep the Grizzlies in this game , as he recorded 17 points ( 6 - 15 FG , 5 - 6 FT ) and eight rebounds in 34 minutes .
#Text=He 's had a nice stretch of two games , combining for 44 points and 19 rebounds over that span .
#Text=Mike Conley reached double figures as well , posting 11 points of his own , but he seemed to struggle with his shot , going just 4 - of - 11 from the field and 0 - for - 2 from deep .
#Text=Coming off the bench , rookie Jordan Adams added 13 points ( 6 - 8 FG , 1 - 1 3Pt ) in 23 minutes .
#Text=The points were a new season - high for the rookie .
#Text=The Jazz 's next game will be on the road against the Boston Celtics on Wednesday , while the Grizzlies will travel to Houston to play the Rockets on Wednesday .
